    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1425"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1425">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/332.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Carothers</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]<note n="125" xml:id="d1425fn125"
                            >Communicated to the Spanish Ambassador June 23, 1914.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Relative your telegram about forced loan 500,000 pesos at Tampico, Carranza says
                    that he has not authorized it and has issued orders to General Caballero not to
                    collect it. Carranza has also ordered investigation as to persecution of Spanish
                    subjects at Monterey and promised to have it stopped.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carothers</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
